The Commissioner of Police, Ekiti State Command, CP Morenikeji Adesina has directed all the Area Commanders, DPOs, Operational Heads and Intelligence Officers to ensure adequate deployment of operatives to all the strategic points across the State to forestall any form of breach of security during the festivity. This is contained in a statement by the PPRO, ASP Sunday Abutu. According to the statement, CP Adesina, who felicitated with the good people of Ekiti State, especially the Christian faithful, on the occasion of the 2022 Easter celebration, urged them to celebrate with modesty. The CP ordered officers deployed to strategic locations to be professional in the discharge of their duties. He assured citizens of adequate security before, during and after the Easter celebration. He urged them to be security conscious, vigilant and report any untoward incident or happening observed in their locality to the nearest Police Station or call 08062335577.